{
  "id": "019d2f1b-ff59-78e1-92b5-95576d50d950",
  "content": "# BM25 Hybrid Search — Brainstorm Design Decisions (2026-03-27)\n\n## Approach Selected: Composable Pipeline with Registry (Approach C)\n\nRejected Approach A (Monolithic HybridRetriever) — perpetuates architectural limitation, combinatorial explosion for benchmarking.\nRejected Approach B (Middleware/Chain) — shape mismatch, retrieval stages are a DAG not a chain, can't parallelize searchers.\n\n## 13 Design Decisions\n\n### D1: Four Stage Traits\nSearcher, Fusion, Expander, Reranker — each behind an async trait. Searchers run in parallel, fusion combines, expander enriches, reranker re-scores.\n\n### D2: RankedSet with CandidateScores\nEach candidate carries component scores (vector, bm25, graph, fusion, rerank) for diagnostics + a single final_score for ordering. Component scores are never compared across types.\n\n### D3: Generic ComponentRegistry\nOne generic `ComponentRegistry<T: ?Sized>` serves all stage types. Maps name → factory function. Adding a new component = implement trait + register (2 steps).\n\n### D4: RetrievalPipeline implements Retriever\nThe composable pipeline implements the existing Retriever trait. RagPipeline sees no change — it still calls retriever.retrieve(). Internal composition is transparent.\n\n### D5: FullTextSearchable as separate trait\nFollows the pattern of QueryableStore / TemporalStore / GraphStore as independent traits. LiteStore implements via TantivyIndex, PostgresStore via tsvector.\n\n### D6: Tantivy for LiteStore\ntantivy 0.22 (pure Rust, no C deps). Index at .corvia/cache/tantivy/. Code-aware tokenizer for snake_case/CamelCase/file paths. Index is a cache — corvia rebuild reconstructs.\n\n### D7: tsvector for PostgresStore\nGenerated tsvector column + GIN index. No additional dependency — native PostgreSQL full-text search.\n\n### D8: RagConfig extended with [rag.pipeline] section\nBackward compatible — if [rag.pipeline] absent, falls back to legacy rag.retriever field.\n\n### D9: Hot-swap via ArcSwap\nSame pattern as HNSW blue-green rebuild. Config change → validate_and_build → atomic swap. Invalid config rejected, old pipeline continues.\n\n### D10: Fusion contract — output [0,1]\nEvery Fusion implementation MUST output final_score in [0.0, 1.0]. Enforced by debug_assert. Critical because GraphExpander uses final_score in blend formula.\n\n### D11: Backward-compatible RetrievalMetrics\nExtend with Optional fields (serde-safe), don't replace. New: bm25_latency_ms, bm25_results, fusion_method, fusion_latency_ms, stages.\n\n### D12: Graceful degradation\nPartial searcher failure → continue with remaining. All fail → error. Tantivy missing → degrade to vector-only.\n\n### D13: Cold tier in tantivy not HNSW\nBM25 can surface cold entries that vector search cannot find. Access triggers tier promotion (cold → warm). BM25 as cold-entry rescue mechanism.",
